Originally, when there are multiple file types presented, ag only takes the last one as its file type. But the user want to search all the file types. e.g. when i type `ag --cpp --cc what_i_want`, ag only searches for c files. But the user wants to seach both c and cpp files.
Separate ignores that start with a slash from the rest. We'll need to search them differently.
Add dir name to ignores. Fix bug where multiple paths could cause root_ignores to leak memory or behave weirdly.
